The paper proposes a novel model for approximating Bayesian neural networks for data streams, which involves deep learning techniques and probabilistic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves experiments with semantic segmentation, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
